com.blukii.sdk.config

Class DataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blukii.sdk.config.DataManager

  • public final class DataManager
extends java.lang.Object

    This class is the central logic to handle all data driven actions.

    From here you can start calls to blukii cloud and handle BlukiiData actions.

    Get the DataManager instance by calling BlukiiController.getConfigDataManager()

    Important:Most of DataManager class functions need to be logged in. See BlukiiCloud for more information.

    See Also:
    BlukiiController, BlukiiCloud, BlukiiData, BlukiiDataItem

      • isOfflineSync

        public boolean isOfflineSync()

        Checks if data sync (see sync(OnSyncListener) will load full cloud config data for offline usage.

        If offline sync is true, data sync is loading full set of config data from blukii Manager for all user owned blukiis.

        Otherwise, status data is loaded only (also for all blukiis). For loading full blukii data call loadBlukii(String, OnLoadBlukiiListener) for single blukiis.

        Returns:
        true, if data sync loads offline data
        See Also:
        sync(OnSyncListener)
